message.body: @the_beta64_fanLIVE Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Z, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (Analog Stick), Cup, Cdown, Cleft, Cright (C Stick), and Dup, Ddown, Dleft, Dright, (D Pad). Typos work too!

fragments.text: @the_beta64_fanLIVE Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Z, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (Analog Stick), Cup, Cdown, Cleft, Cright (C Stick), and Dup, Ddown, Dleft, Dright, (D Pad). Typos work too!

message.body: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

fragments.text: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

fragments.text: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

fragments.text: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

fragments.text: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

message.body: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

fragments.text: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

message.body: Alternatively, you can spam votes to make sure your vote always stays in the pool. You can switch sides whenever you want. Basic mode executes inputs are they are received from chat, it is limited for some tasks, while advanced can be used to do a sequence of very precise inputs. Current mode is Advanced mode.

fragments.text: Alternatively, you can spam votes to make sure your vote always stays in the pool. You can switch sides whenever you want. Basic mode executes inputs are they are received from chat, it is limited for some tasks, while advanced can be used to do a sequence of very precise inputs. Current mode is Advanced mode.

fragments.text: @rainchus Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Z, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (Analog Stick), Cup, Cdown, Cleft, Cright (C Stick), and Dup, Ddown, Dleft, Dright, (D Pad). Typos work too!

message.body: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

fragments.text: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

fragments.text: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

fragments.text: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

fragments.text: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

message.body: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

fragments.text: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

message.body: Alternatively, you can spam votes to make sure your vote always stays in the pool. You can switch sides whenever you want. Basic mode executes inputs are they are received from chat, it is limited for some tasks, while advanced can be used to do a sequence of very precise inputs. Current mode is Advanced mode.

message.body: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

fragments.text: Up to 3 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Cright will press the B Button, pull Up on the Analog Stick and pull Right on the C Stick. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Analog Stick.

message.body: @JonnyGamble Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Z, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (Analog Stick), Cup, Cdown, Cleft, Cright (C Stick), and Dup, Ddown, Dleft, Dright, (D Pad). Typos work too!

fragments.text: @JonnyGamble Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Z, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (Analog Stick), Cup, Cdown, Cleft, Cright (C Stick), and Dup, Ddown, Dleft, Dright, (D Pad). Typos work too!

message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

fragments.text: Normal duration of inputs is 266 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

fragments.text: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

fragments.text: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: "A Wait *255" will press the A Button for 266 milliseconds then wait for another 266 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times.

message.body: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

fragments.text: You can type Basic or Advanced to vote to change input modes. It is needed at least 75% of votes on either side to change input modes, votes are removed from the pool after 5 minutes. After that, you'll have to vote again to have your vote readded to the pool.

message.body: Alternatively, you can spam votes to make sure your vote always stays in the pool. You can switch sides whenever you want. Basic mode executes inputs are they are received from chat, it is limited for some tasks, while advanced can be used to do a sequence of very precise inputs. Current mode is Advanced mode.

message.body: Example: "Up+Right+B;2000 A+Z+Down;1000 *5" Will pull Up and Right on the Analog Stick and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and Z Buttons and pull Down on the Analog Stick for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and "*5" will repeat that macro 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.
